item.title: Hell Gette - (##) | Annka Kultys Gallery
item.description: The first emojis were created in 1999 by Japanese designer Shigetaka Kurita for a local telecoms company. Over the two decades since, they’ve mounted a stealth takeover of the world’s written conversation, and along the way, found their way into the permanent collection at MoMA. Some more emoji art can currently be found up a staircase off the Hackney Road, with a small exhibition of paintings from Kazakhstan-born German artist, Hell Gette.
